CatDescriptText: Joyce Ingram, domestic, 120 Lynnwood Avenue, Sewickley, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1959, pg. 6 with question: "With Mayor Lawrence performing his duties as Governor in Harrisburg, do you believe the Democratic party in Pittsburgh will be weakened by his absence?" answer reads: "No, I don't, and one of the reasons I think this way is because I come from a family of Democrats.  The people have faith in Democratic party and therefore they support it.
